nterreligious projects remains scant in comparison. This volume offers a unique contribution that not only looks at several of the challenges and implications faced by religious and interreligious peacebuilders but also provides concrete examples of new models and tools for monitoring and evaluating religious and interreligious peacebuilding projects. In doing so, this volume serves as a tool and point of reference for individuals and organizations developing and implementing interreligious dialogue and peacebuilding projects.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aDialog. 4aFriedenskonsolidierung. 4aInterreligiosität. 4aMethodik. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  aInterreligiosity.  abest practice.  adialogue.  apeacebuilding.1 aAbu-Nimer, Mohammed, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbu-Nimer, Mohammed, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCohen, Shana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEhsan, Khaled, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarred, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerrington, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHume, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNelson, Renáta Katalin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNelson, Renáta Katalin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNeufeldt, Reina C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPul, Hippolyt, econtributor